title>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/18/02 6:24:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> Ripfang, in my opinion you should sell the GJBS, Wurmy, and Centi LS, and buy two Lamentations (9/19 6str 6sta 20hp) or one Lamentation and a Frostbringer (12/22 7ac procs 60dd and an AC debuff on target). On my server a Lammy is 2k, and Frosty is 6k. And use those SCHW's. 22% haste is equal to 2.2 seconds off you weapons. (10% haste = 1 delay)<br><br>You might have to spend some of your hard earned cash to buy the 2 weapons (but probably only if you're going with the Lam/Frost combo)... but it's worth it. The hp you get from 2 Lammy's is about 90.4hp at level 60. 6sta on each Lammy... 1sta equals 4.2hp at lvl 60 for a ranger, so 6 times 4.2hp = 25.2hp, and add the 20 raw hp on the Lammy... so thats 20 + 20 + 25.2 + 25.2 = 90.4 rounded to 90 hitpoints gain for the 2 Lammy combo. But if you want Frostbringer, it makes a great primary weapon for the proc and the damage bonus (you'll be hitting nicely as the Frosty has 12dmg). <br><br>Hope that helped. <p><img src=http://members.aol.com/sephir0th18/images/crit.jpg><Br> Zaztik Sureshot --- 60 Warder<Br> Proud Member of Shining Alliance<Br> <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82601>Inspect Zaztik</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uytrill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ytrill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/18/02 9:56:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.kc.rr.com/witchdoctor/ytrill7a.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What haste percentage REALLY means</span><hr size=1> How haste works is probably the single most misunderstood facet of combat mechanics in EQ.<br><br>First, haste doesn't reduce weapon delay by a fixed number per haste percentage. The amount of the reduction in delay, expressed as a whole number rather than a percentage, depends entirely on the unhasted delay of the weapon for any haste value.<br><br>Second, commonly accepted haste values don't really describe delay reduction, but rather an increase in the number of swings per unit time. Because the number of swings increases, haste <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   effectively</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> reduces the delay of a weapon - but not by a fixed amount, nor by the haste percentage itself.<br><br>Let's use a Wurmy and FBSS as an example. FBSS haste is usually said to be 21%. Some people say it's 17%. Both figures are correct, depending on whether you think of haste as an increase in swings per time or a reduction in delay.<br><br>We'll start with the most commonly accepted number of 21%. With a delay of 40, an unhasted Wurmy swings every 4 seconds, or 15 times a minute; hasted with an FBSS, it swings 21% more times a minute, or approximately 18 times a minute total.<br><br>The correct formula for calculating effective delay reduction is (unhasted weapon delay/(1 + haste item percentage). Let's stick with the Wurmy/FBSS combo to illustrate. The calculation would be:<br><br>Unhasted Wurmy delay = 40/1 + FBSS haste = .21<br><br>40/1.21 = 33<br><br>An FBSS therefore effectively reduces the Wurmy's delay by 7, not by 2.1 as Zaztik's assertion would predict. Even for a Lammy, the delay reduction is 3 (19/1.21 = 16, rounded up).<br><br>Also note that the delay reduction expressed as a percentage is 7/40 = 17.5 percent, not 21%. That's why you still occasionally hear people say that the FBSS is a 17% haste item.<br><br>Hope this helps. <p><font size=2, face=legends, arial><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27521><b>Ytrill Stonebow</b></a><br>Outrider<br>Destiny Awaits - E'ci</font></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uytrill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ytrill</A> at: 7/18/02 10:00:05 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uzaztik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zaztik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/19/02 10:14:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What haste percentage REALLY means</span><hr size=1> Yeah, i just realized I made that mistake.. I got an email from a friend that has a good theory on haste. This is it...<br><br>Percent means &quot;parts out of 100&quot; <br>So 100% is 100 parts out of 100, or 100/100 <br>Thus 100% translates into 1. <br>So 1+100% would be 2. <br><br>Using his formula, a lammy (9/19) at 40% haste would be... <br>19/(1+.4) <br>= 19/1.4 <br>= 13.57 <br>Rounded, you'd effectivly be 9/14<br><br><br>Sorry bout that, I don't know what the heck got into me, I shouldn't type when it's so late at night <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br> <p><img src=http://members.aol.com/sephir0th18/images/crit.jpg><Br> Veteran Zaztik Sureshot --- 60th Warder<Br> Proud Member of Shining Alliance<Br> <a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82601>Inspect Zaztik</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uytrill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>