 for help please... <br><br>I solo a LOT as I seriously dislike sitting and yelling for groups but given the opportunity I dont mind grouping. I want a weap combo that will give me the MAX damage..not taunt not proc (unreliable at best and I have a Venemous axe) I want pure damage as fast and hard as I can get. Any advice would be greatly appreciated. Oh and I dont have a wurmy but I do have Centi LS, Capt guards mallet, crystaline ss, venemous axe, even a solid 2hs.<br><br>Thanks  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uytrill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ytrill</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Outrider</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(8/19/02 5:48:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/ytrill/ytrill7a.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: weapons combos</span><hr size=1> Braask:<br><br>The short answer is, it depends on your level and the level/AC of the monsters you're fighting.<br><br>Before your late 40s or early 50s at earliest, there is not enough of a damage bonus to justify using a faster weapon over a Wurmy...unless it also has a REALLY good ratio, or other characteristics that make it more desirable (such as Earthcaller).<br><br>The closer you get to 60, however, the higher your damage bonus becomes. At some point -- and this is highly variable -- faster weapons will outperform slower ones with a better ratio. This is because if you're fighting MOBs with a ton of mitigation AC relative to your ATK rating, a faster weapon will hit for the minimum (1 + damage bonus) more often than a slower weapon will. This phenomenon is most noticeable against uber MOBs, where even level 60 players in end-game gear frequently hit for 11s with the main hand. However, even in your high 50s, Wurmslayer can outdamage faster weapons against typical XP-grind MOBs.<br><br>So, the &quot;faster weapon in main hand&quot; answer is a paradigm that may hold true sometimes, or even most of the time: but not always. Best thing to do is parse your damage with your available combos, in hunting situations you usually find yourself in, and use the results to make a decision that's right for YOU. I wish I could give you a more specific answer. <p><font size=2, face=legends, arial><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27521><b>Ytrill Stonebow</b></a><br>Outrider<br>Destiny Awaits - E'ci</font></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uytrill.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ytrill</A> at: 8/19/02 5:50:06 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#00000F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub59.ezboard.com/uralamwen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ralamwen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(8/19/02 7:48:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub59.ezboard.com/feqrangers65329frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: weapons combos</span><hr size=1> That is a good answer.. I tried alot of combos until I found one that is right for me... i use a Centi ss and a jagged blade of mourning, I will be getting another wurmy soon, because I Love the dmg output.. YOU make a choice on what YOU find out.... it is alot better that way <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><HTML><BODY><a Target="_top" href="http://www.flamingtext.com/ezb.html" ><img src="http://ezb.flamingtext.com/ezb/2002/08/02/flamingtext_com_1028314510_23956.jpg" border=0 alt="Image by FlamingText.com"></a><br>Image by <a href="http